{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892939927,"sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b77c474001K1iMe43tLZCxl2","messageID":"msg_d7b77ba77001WTLuG073ZdHCZt","sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-148f5382dfb0436193b0f81efd8c771e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Go Unit Tests for pkg/workloadmanager\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This proposal outlines a comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module to improve code quality, reliability, and maintainability of the AgentCube workload management system.\n6: \n7: **AR:** AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n8: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`\n9: **Language:** Go\n10: **Size:** L\n11: \n12: ## Purpose\n13: \n14: The workloadmanager module is a critical component responsible for managing sandbox lifecycles, Kubernetes resource reconciliation, and garbage collection. Currently, test coverage is partial and concentrated in some submodules (gc, handler, api, config) while the core reconciliation logic lacks comprehensive unit tests.\n15: \n16: This testing initiative aims to:\n17: \n18: 1. **Ensure correctness** of reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n19: 2. **Validate error handling** paths and edge cases\n20: 3. **Test condition management** and status updates\n21: 4. **Cover finalizer management** for resource cleanup\n22: 5. **Verify predicate logic** for event filtering\n23: 6. **Provide regression protection** for future changes\n24: \n25: ## Scope\n26: \n27: ### In-Scope Components\n28: \n29: The proposal focuses on the most critical and currently untested components:\n30: \n31: 1. **Controller Reconciler** (`controller/reconciler/`):\n32:    - `codeinterpreter.go` - Core reconciliation logic (primary focus)\n33:    - `status.go` - Condition management utilities\n34:    - `finalizers.go` - Finalizer management\n35:    - `predicates.go` - Event filtering predicates\n36:    - `errors.go` - Error handling\n37:    - `controller.go` - Controller setup functions\n38: \n39: 2. **Handler Extensions** (`handler/`):\n40:    - `sandbox.go` - SandboxHandler with deletion logic (supplementary)\n41: \n42: 3. **Server Setup** (`server/`):\n43:    - `server.go` - Server initialization (supplementary)\n44: \n45: ### Out-of-Scope\n46: \n47: - Integration tests with real Kubernetes clusters (separate effort)\n48: - End-to-end API tests (covered by existing handler tests)\n49: - Performance/load testing\n50: - Modules with existing adequate test coverage (gc, handler, api, config)\n51: \n52: ## Test Strategy\n53: \n54: ### Testing Framework\n55: \n56: - **Primary:** `testing` package (standard library)\n57: - **Assertions:** `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert` and `require`\n58: - **Mocking:** `github.com/stretchr/testify/mock` for controller-runtime interfaces\n59: - **Kubernetes Testing:** `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for realistic scenario testing\n60: - **Fake Clients:** `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client/fake` for mock Kubernetes API interactions\n61: \n62: ### Test Categories\n63: \n64: #### 1. Unit Tests (Primary Focus)\n65: - Isolated function-level testing\n66: - Mock all external dependencies\n67: - Fast execution (< 1s per test)\n68: - High coverage of code paths\n69: \n70: #### 2. Reconciler Tests (Critical)\n71: - Full reconciliation cycle testing\n72: - Status condition updates\n73: - Error handling and retry logic\n74: - Finalizer lifecycle\n75: \n76: #### 3. Integration-Style Tests\n77: - Use fake client but test real logic\n78: - Test interaction between reconciler components\n79: - Verify Kubernetes resource creation/updates\n80: \n81: ### Coverage Targets\n82: \n83: | Component | Target Coverage | Priority |\n84: |-----------|----------------|----------|\n85: | `codeinterpreter.go` | 85%+ | P0 (Critical) |\n86: | `status.go` | 90%+ | P0 (Critical) |\n87: | `finalizers.go` | 90%+ | P0 (Critical) |\n88: | `predicates.go` | 95%+ | P1 (High) |\n89: | `errors.go` | 80%+ | P1 (High) |\n90: | `controller.go` | 70%+ | P2 (Medium) |\n91: | `sandbox.go` | 75%+ | P2 (Medium) |\n92: | `server.go` | 70%+ | P2 (Medium) |\n93: \n94: ## Detailed Test Plans\n95: \n96: ### 1. CodeInterpreter Reconciler Tests (`codeinterpreter_reconciler_test.go`)\n97: \n98: **Test Scenarios:**\n99: \n100: #### Reconcile Method\n101: - [ ] Successful reconciliation of new CodeInterpreter\n102: - [ ] Reconciliation with existing sandbox (no changes)\n103: - [ ] Reconciliation with sandbox spec changes (update)\n104: - [ ] Reconciliation when sandbox not ready (requeue)\n105: - [ ] Reconciliation of deleted CodeInterpreter (cleanup)\n106: - [ ] Handling of missing CodeInterpreter (not found)\n107: - [ ] Adding finalizer on first reconciliation\n108: - [ ] Validation failure handling (invalid spec)\n109: - [ ] Sandbox creation failure handling\n110: - [ ] Sandbox update failure handling\n111: - [ ] Status update failure handling\n112: - [ ] Conflict error handling (retry logic)\n113: - [ ] ObservedGeneration tracking\n114: \n115: #### Reconcile Delete Method\n116: - [ ] Successful sandbox deletion\n117: - [ ] Handling missing sandbox (not found)\n118: - [ ] Sandbox deletion failure\n119: - [ ] Finalizer removal\n120: - [ ] Finalizer removal failure\n121: - [ ] Event recording for deletion\n122: \n123: #### Reconcile Sandbox Method\n124: - [ ] Create sandbox when not exists\n125: - [ ] Update sandbox when exists and spec changed\n126: - [ ] No update when spec unchanged\n127: - [ ] Skip update when pod being deleted\n128: - [ ] Error handling for Get failures\n129: \n130: #### Build Pod Spec Method\n131: - [ ] Build pod spec with custom image\n132: - [ ] Use default image when not specified\n133: - [ ] Include environment variables\n134: - [ ] Include resource limits\n135: - [ ] Handle nil resources\n136: \n137: #### Validate Spec Method\n138: - [ ] Valid spec passes\n139: - [ ] Empty image fails\n140: - [ ] Invalid resource spec handling\n141: \n142: #### Is Ready Method\n143: - [ ] Return true when pod ready\n144: - [ ] Return false when pod not ready\n145: - [ ] Return false when pod not found\n146: - [ ] Return false when pod being deleted\n147: \n148: #### Helper Functions\n149: - [ ] GetSandboxName generates correct name\n150: - [ ] convertEnvVars handles empty/nil env\n151: - [ ] convertResources handles limits/requests\n152: - [ ] podSpecsEqual comparison logic\n153: \n154: ### 2. Status Management Tests (`status_test.go`)\n155: \n156: **Test Scenarios:**\n157: \n158: #### Set Condition\n159: - [ ] Add new condition to empty slice\n160: - [ ] Update existing condition with different status\n161: - [ ] Update existing condition with same status (update time only)\n162: - [ ] Update existing condition with different reason/message\n163: - [ ] Handle nil conditions pointer\n164: \n165: #### Get Condition\n166: - [ ] Find existing condition by type\n167: - [ ] Return nil for non-existent condition\n168: - [ ] Handle empty conditions slice\n169: \n170: #### Condition Checkers\n171: - [ ] IsReady returns true when Ready=True\n172: - [ ] IsReady returns false when Ready=False/missing\n173: - [ ] IsAvailable returns true when Available=True\n174: - [ ] IsProgressing returns true when Progressing=True\n175: - [ ] HasError returns true when Error=True\n176: \n177: #### Condition Setters\n178: - [ ] SetReadyCondition sets correct status\n179: - [ ] SetErrorCondition includes error message\n180: - [ ] ClearErrorCondition removes error condition\n181: - [ ] SetProgressingCondition sets correct status\n182: - [ ] SetAvailableCondition sets correct status\n183: - [ ] SetSandboxCreatedCondition sets correct status\n184: \n185: #### Condition Utilities\n186: - [ ] GetConditionMessage returns message or empty string\n187: - [ ] GetConditionReason returns reason or empty string\n188: \n189: ### 3. Finalizers Tests (`finalizers_test.go`)\n190: \n191: **Test Scenarios:**\n192: \n193: #### Add Finalizer\n194: - [ ] Add finalizer to object without finalizers\n195: - [ ] Add finalizer when already exists (no-op)\n196: - [ ] Add multiple finalizers\n197: - [ ] Patch failure handling\n198: \n199: #### Remove Finalizer\n200: - [ ] Remove finalizer from object\n201: - [ ] No-op when finalizer not present\n202: - [ ] Remove finalizer from middle of list\n203: - [ ] Remove last finalizer\n204: - [ ] Patch failure handling\n205: \n206: #### Has Finalizer\n207: - [ ] Return true when finalizer present\n208: - [ ] Return false when finalizer absent\n209: - [ ] Handle empty finalizers slice\n210: \n211: #### Owner References\n212: - [ ] GetOwnerReference returns UID when found\n213: - [ ] GetOwnerReference returns not found when missing\n214: - [ ] Match by APIVersion and Kind\n215: \n216: ### 4. Predicates Tests (`predicates_test.go`)\n217: \n218: **Test Scenarios:**\n219: \n220: #### ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n221: - [ ] Update returns true when generation changes\n222: - [ ] Update returns false when generation same\n223: - [ ] Update returns false when nil objects\n224: - [ ] Create returns true\n225: - [ ] Delete returns true\n226: \n227: #### LabelChangedPredicate\n228: - [ ] Update returns true when labels differ\n229: - [ ] Update returns true when label count differs\n230: - [ ] Update returns false when labels same\n231: - [ ] Handle nil label maps\n232: \n233: #### AnnotationChangedPredicate\n234: - [ ] Update returns true when annotations differ\n235: - [ ] Update returns true when annotation count differs\n236: - [ ] Update returns false when annotations same\n237: - [ ] Handle nil annotation maps\n238: \n239: #### PauseAnnotationPredicate\n240: - [ ] Update returns false when paused annotation present\n241: - [ ] Update returns true when paused annotation absent\n242: - [ ] Update returns false when paused=false\n243: - [ ] Create returns true when not paused\n244: - [ ] Delete returns true\n245: \n246: #### Utility Functions\n247: - [ ] IsBeingDeleted returns true with deletion timestamp\n248: - [ ] HasOwnerReference returns true when UID matches\n249: - [ ] AddOwnerReference adds controller reference\n250: - [ ] AddLabels merges new labels with existing\n251: - [ ] AddAnnotations merges new annotations with existing\n252: - [ ] IsPodReady returns true when PodReady condition true\n253: - [ ] GetPodCondition finds specific condition\n254: \n255: ### 5. Error Handling Tests (`errors_test.go`)\n256: \n257: **Test Scenarios:**\n258: \n259: #### ReconcilerError\n260: - [ ] Error() formats message without wrapped error\n261: - [ ] Error() formats message with wrapped error\n262: - [ ] Unwrap() returns wrapped error\n263: - [ ] Retryable flag preserved\n264: \n265: #### Error Constructors\n266: - [ ] NewReconcilerError creates error with all fields\n267: - [ ] NewValidationFailedError creates non-retryable error\n268: - [ ] NewSandboxCreateFailedError creates retryable error\n269: - [ ] NewSandboxUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n270: - [ ] NewSandboxDeleteFailedError creates retryable error\n271: - [ ] NewStatusUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n272: - [ ] NewFinalizerFailedError creates retryable error\n273: \n274: ### 6. Controller Setup Tests (`controller_test.go`)\n275: \n276: **Test Scenarios:**\n277: \n278: #### Controller Config\n279: - [ ] DefaultControllerConfig returns sensible defaults\n280: - [ ] All expected fields populated\n281: \n282: #### Controller Manager\n283: - [ ] NewControllerManager creates manager successfully\n284: - [ ] Manager configured with correct options\n285: - [ ] Error handling for manager creation failure\n286: \n287: #### Setup Functions\n288: - [ ] SetupWithManager sets up both reconcilers\n289: - [ ] setupAgentRuntimeReconciler configures controller\n290: - [ ] setupCodeInterpreterReconciler configures controller\n291: - [ ] Error handling for setup failures\n292: \n293: #### Utilities\n294: - [ ] GetSandboxName generates correct format\n295: - [ ] SandboxResult struct initialization\n296: \n297: ### 7. Sandbox Handler Tests (`sandbox_handler_test.go`)\n298: \n299: **Test Scenarios:**\n300: \n301: #### Handle Delete Sandbox\n302: - [ ] Successfully delete sandbox with valid session ID\n303: - [ ] Return error when session ID empty\n304: - [ ] Return 404 when session not found\n305: - [ ] Handle SandboxClaim deletion\n306: - [ ] Handle Sandbox deletion\n307: - [ ] Return 500 for store errors\n308: - [ ] Handle K8s delete failures\n309: - [ ] Cleanup store even when K8s delete fails\n310: - [ ] Handle not found from K8s (already deleted)\n311: \n312: ### 8. Server Tests (`server_test.go`)\n313: \n314: **Test Scenarios:**\n315: \n316: #### Server Initialization\n317: - [ ] NewServer creates server with correct configuration\n318: - [ ] Server registers expected routes\n319: - [ ] Server uses correct middleware\n320: - [ ] Server health endpoint returns 200\n321: \n322: ## Implementation Plan\n323: \n324: ### Phase 1: Core Reconciler (Week 1-2)\n325: 1. Implement `status_test.go` (foundation for other tests)\n326: 2. Implement `finalizers_test.go`\n327: 3. Implement `errors_test.go`\n328: 4. Setup test utilities and helpers\n329: \n330: ### Phase 2: CodeInterpreter Reconciler (Week 2-3)\n331: 1. Implement `codeinterpreter_reconciler_test.go`\n332: 2. Focus on main reconciliation logic\n333: 3. Cover success and error paths\n334: \n335: ### Phase 3: Predicates and Utilities (Week 3)\n336: 1. Implement `predicates_test.go`\n337: 2. Implement `controller_test.go`\n338: 3. Add any missing utility tests\n339: \n340: ### Phase 4: Handler and Server (Week 4)\n341: 1. Implement `sandbox_handler_test.go`\n342: 2. Implement `server_test.go`\n343: 3. Review and fill gaps\n344: \n345: ### Phase 5: Validation and Coverage (Week 4)\n346: 1. Run full test suite\n347: 2. Verify coverage targets\n348: 3. Add missing edge case tests\n349: 4. Documentation and cleanup\n350: \n351: ## Testing Utilities\n352: \n353: To support the test suite, we'll create shared utilities:\n354: \n355: ```go\n356: // testutil/reconciler_test.go\n357: package testutil\n358: \n359: // Helper functions for creating test objects\n360: func NewTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n361: func NewTestPod(name, namespace string) *corev1.Pod\n362: func NewFakeClient() client.Client\n363: \n364: // Helpers for assertions\n365: func AssertConditionEqual(t *testing.T, conditions []metav1.Condition, expectedType, expectedStatus string)\n366: func AssertHasFinalizer(t *testing.T, obj client.Object, finalizer string)\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ## CI/CD Integration\n370: \n371: ### Pre-commit Checks\n372: - Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` on every commit\n373: - Fail if coverage drops below threshold (70% overall, 80% for new code)\n374: \n375: ### Pipeline Requirements\n376: - All tests must pass before merge\n377: - Generate coverage reports and upload to coverage service\n378: - Run tests on PR creation and update\n379: \n380: ### Coverage Enforcement\n381: - Set minimum coverage thresholds in CI\n382: - Block merges that reduce coverage\n383: - Generate coverage badges for README\n384: \n385: ## Impact Analysis\n386: \n387: ### Benefits\n388: 1. **Improved Reliability**: Catch bugs early in development cycle\n389: 2. **Faster Development**: Refactor with confidence using test safety net\n390: 3. **Better Documentation**: Tests serve as executable documentation\n391: 4. **Reduced Debugging Time**: Quick failure identification\n392: 5. **Regression Prevention**: Ensure existing functionality works after changes\n393: \n394: ### Risks\n395: 1. **Time Investment**: Initial test writing requires significant effort\n396: 2. **Maintenance Overhead**: Tests need updates when code changes\n397: 3. **False Confidence**: Tests only cover what they test; gaps may exist\n398: 4. **Test Brittleness**: Over-specific tests may break with unrelated changes\n399: \n400: ### Mitigation Strategies\n401: 1. Start with critical paths and expand iteratively\n402: 2. Focus on behavior testing over implementation details\n403: 3. Use table-driven tests for comprehensive coverage\n404: 4. Regular test maintenance and refactoring\n405: \n406: ## Alternatives Considered\n407: \n408: ### Alternative 1: Integration Tests Only\n409: - **Pros**: Tests real system behavior\n410: - **Cons**: Slower, harder to isolate failures, complex setup\n411: - **Verdict**: Complementary, not replacement for unit tests\n412: \n413: ### Alternative 2: Property-Based Testing\n414: - **Pros**: Finds edge cases unit tests miss\n415: - **Cons**: Steeper learning curve, more complex setup\n416: - **Verdict**: Consider for future enhancement\n417: \n418: ### Alternative 3: Minimal Testing (Current State)\n419: - **Pros**: No upfront investment\n420: - **Cons**: High bug risk, slower development, technical debt\n421: - **Verdict**: Unsustainable for critical path code\n422: \n423: ## Dependencies\n424: \n425: ### Required Packages\n426: - `github.com/stretchr/testify` (already in go.mod)\n427: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` (already in go.mod)\n428: - `k8s.io/client-go` (already in go.mod)\n429: \n430: ### Test Data\n431: - Use existing CRD definitions from `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n432: - Mock client-go and controller-runtime interfaces\n433: \n434: ## Success Criteria\n435: \n436: 1. All proposed test files implemented and passing\n437: 2. Overall test coverage for `pkg/workloadmanager` ≥ 80%\n438: 3. Critical components (`codeinterpreter.go`, `status.go`, `finalizers.go`) ≥ 85% coverage\n439: 4. All tests run in < 30 seconds total\n440: 5. No flaky tests (100% pass rate over 100 runs)\n441: 6. Tests integrated into CI/CD pipeline\n442: 7. Code review approval from 2 reviewers\n443: \n444: ## Open Questions\n445: \n446: 1. Should we use `envtest` for more realistic integration-style tests?\n447: 2. What should be the minimum coverage threshold enforced in CI?\n448: 3. Should we add benchmark tests for performance-critical paths?\n449: \n450: ## Timeline\n451: \n452: | Week | Milestone |\n453: |------|-----------|\n454: | 1 | Phase 1: Core utilities (status, finalizers, errors) |\n455: | 2 | Phase 1 complete, start Phase 2 (reconciler) |\n456: | 3 | Phase 2 complete, start Phase 3 (predicates) |\n457: | 4 | Phase 3 & 4 complete, Phase 5 (validation) |\n458: | 5 | Code review, refinements, final documentation |\n459: \n460: Total estimated effort: **5 weeks** (1 developer)\n461: \n462: ## Related Documentation\n463: \n464: - [client-go library](../deployment/client-go.md) - Kubernetes client interfaces\n465: - [workloadmanager design](./design.md) - Module architecture\n466: - [GC design](./design-gc.md) - Garbage collector design\n467: \n468: ## References\n469: \n470: - [Go Testing Best Practices](https://go.dev/doc/tutorial/add-a-test)\n471: - [Kubernetes Controller Runtime Testing](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/testing.html)\n472: - [Testify Documentation](https://github.com/stretchr/testify)\n\n(End of file - total 472 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Go Unit Tests for pkg/workloadmanager\n\n## Overview\n\nThis proposal outlines a comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module to improve code quality, reliability, and maintainability of the AgentCube workload management system.\n\n**AR:** AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe workloadmanager module is a critical component responsible for managing sandbox lifecycles, Kubernetes resource reconciliation, and garbage collection. Currently, test coverage is partial and concentrated in some submodules (gc, handler, api, config) while the core reconciliation logic lacks comprehensive unit tests.\n\nThis testing initiative aims to:\n\n1. **Ensure correctness** of reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **Validate error handling** paths and edge cases\n3. **Test condition management** and status updates","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775892939917,"end":1775892939924}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775892939953,"sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b77c4970017CvJSmm34Ww3lz","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b77ba77001WTLuG073ZdHCZt","sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":21001,"input":1975,"output":83,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":18943}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775892942999,"sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b77d095001LscBaThSuCHk96","messageID":"msg_d7b77c4c4001Ojo7QrAWrkHjYf","sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892943944,"sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b77d428001lNsOrK24rEImBt","messageID":"msg_d7b77c4c4001Ojo7QrAWrkHjYf","sessionID":"ses_2848892f0ffe04i82DWLDMHtoJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4d5d7b5ce02848e6a62f884aab3dc994","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec: AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Module: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n6: Language: Go\n7: Size: L\n8: Task: Add comprehensive unit tests for untested components\n9: \n10: ## Requirements\n11: \n12: ### REQ-001: Unit tests for auth/k8s_auth.go\n13: \n14: **Description:** Implement unit tests for K8sAuthenticator and TokenCache components.\n15: \n16: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n17: \n18: #### SCENARIO-001: K8sAuthenticator authenticates valid token\n19: ```gherkin\n20: GIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience\n21: AND a valid Kubernetes service account token\n22: WHEN Authenticate is called with the token\n23: THEN the AuthenticationInfo should be returned containing username, UID, and groups\n24: AND no error should be returned\n25: ```\n26: \n27: #### SCENARIO-002: K8sAuthenticator rejects invalid token\n28: ```gherkin\n29: GIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience\n30: AND an invalid/expired Kubernetes token\n31: WHEN Authenticate is called with the invalid token\n32: THEN an error should be returned\n33: AND the error message should indicate authentication failed\n34: ```\n35: \n36: #### SCENARIO-003: K8sAuthenticator handles TokenReview API failure\n37: ```gherkin\n38: GIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface\n39: AND the TokenReview API returns an error\n40: WHEN Authenticate is called\n41: THEN an error should be returned\n42: AND the error should wrap the underlying API error\n43: ```\n44: \n45: #### SCENARIO-004: TokenCache stores and retrieves valid entry\n46: ```gherkin\n47: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 5 minutes\n48: AND an AuthenticationInfo object\n49: WHEN Put is called with a token and the info\n50: AND Get is called with the same token before TTL expires\n51: THEN the AuthenticationInfo should be returned\n52: AND the second return value should be true\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### SCENARIO-005: TokenCache returns false for non-existent token\n56: ```gherkin\n57: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 5 minutes\n58: WHEN Get is called with a token that was never stored\n59: THEN nil should be returned\n60: AND the second return value should be false\n61: ```\n62: \n63: #### SCENARIO-006: TokenCache expires entries after TTL\n64: ```gherkin\n65: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 1 millisecond\n66: AND an AuthenticationInfo object stored with Put\n67: WHEN the cache is waited for 2 milliseconds\n68: AND Get is called with the token\n69: THEN nil should be returned\n70: AND the second return value should be false\n71: ```\n72: \n73: #### SCENARIO-007: TokenCache Delete removes entry\n74: ```gherkin\n75: GIVEN a TokenCache with a stored token entry\n76: WHEN Delete is called with the token\n77: AND Get is called with the same token\n78: THEN nil should be returned\n79: AND the second return value should be false\n80: ```\n81: \n82: #### SCENARIO-008: TokenCache Cleanup removes expired entries\n83: ```gherkin\n84: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 1 millisecond\n85: AND multiple token entries stored\n86: WHEN the cache is waited for 2 milliseconds\n87: AND Cleanup is called\n88: THEN expired entries should be removed from the cache\n89: ```\n90: \n91: #### SCENARIO-009: TokenCache is thread-safe for concurrent reads\n92: ```gherkin\n93: GIVEN a TokenCache with multiple stored entries\n94: AND multiple goroutines calling Get concurrently\n95: THEN no race condition should occur\n96: AND all reads should return consistent results\n97: ```\n98: \n99: #### SCENARIO-010: TokenCache is thread-safe for concurrent writes\n100: ```gherkin\n101: GIVEN a TokenCache\n102: AND multiple goroutines calling Put with different tokens concurrently\n103: THEN no race condition should occur\n104: AND all entries should be stored correctly\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### REQ-002: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/predicates.go\n110: \n111: **Description:** Implement unit tests for event predicates and helper functions.\n112: \n113: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n114: \n115: #### SCENARIO-011: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns true on generation change\n116: ```gherkin\n117: GIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n118: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld generation = 1\n119: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew generation = 2\n120: WHEN Update is called with the event\n121: THEN true should be returned\n122: ```\n123: \n124: #### SCENARIO-012: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns false on same generation\n125: ```gherkin\n126: GIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n127: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld generation = 1\n128: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew generation = 1\n129: WHEN Update is called with the event\n130: THEN false should be returned\n131: ```\n132: \n133: #### SCENARIO-013: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns false on nil objects\n134: ```gherkin\n135: GIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n136: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld = nil\n137: OR ObjectNew = nil\n138: WHEN Update is called with the event\n139: THEN false should be returned\n140: ```\n141: \n142: #### SCENARIO-014: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label added\n143: ```gherkin\n144: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n145: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n146: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"value\", \"newKey\": \"newValue\"}\n147: WHEN Update is called with the event\n148: THEN true should be returned\n149: ```\n150: \n151: #### SCENARIO-015: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label modified\n152: ```gherkin\n153: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n154: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"oldValue\"}\n155: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"newValue\"}\n156: WHEN Update is called with the event\n157: THEN true should be returned\n158: ```\n159: \n160: #### SCENARIO-016: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label removed\n161: ```gherkin\n162: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n163: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key1\": \"value1\", \"key2\": \"value2\"}\n164: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key1\": \"value1\"}\n165: WHEN Update is called with the event\n166: THEN true should be returned\n167: ```\n168: \n169: #### SCENARIO-017: LabelChangedPredicate returns false on unchanged labels\n170: ```gherkin\n171: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n172: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n173: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n174: WHEN Update is called with the event\n175: THEN false should be returned\n176: ```\n177: \n178: #### SCENARIO-018: AnnotationChangedPredicate returns true on annotation change\n179: ```gherkin\n180: GIVEN an AnnotationChangedPredicate\n181: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld annotations = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n182: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew annotations = {\"key\": \"newValue\"}\n183: WHEN Update is called with the event\n184: THEN true should be returned\n185: ```\n186: \n187: #### SCENARIO-019: PauseAnnotationPredicate returns true when not paused\n188: ```gherkin\n189: GIVEN a PauseAnnotationPredicate\n190: AND a CreateEvent with Object annotations = {}\n191: WHEN Create is called with the event\n192: THEN true should be returned\n193: ```\n194: \n195: #### SCENARIO-020: PauseAnnotationPredicate returns false when paused\n196: ```gherkin\n197: GIVEN a PauseAnnotationPredicate\n198: AND a CreateEvent with Object annotations = {\"agentcube.volcano.sh/paused\": \"true\"}\n199: WHEN Create is called with the event\n200: THEN false should be returned\n201: ```\n202: \n203: #### SCENARIO-021: IsBeingDeleted returns true for object with deletion timestamp\n204: ```gherkin\n205: GIVEN a client.Object with DeletionTimestamp set\n206: WHEN IsBeingDeleted is called with the object\n207: THEN true should be returned\n208: ```\n209: \n210: #### SCENARIO-022: IsBeingDeleted returns false for object without deletion timestamp\n211: ```gherkin\n212: GIVEN a client.Object with zero DeletionTimestamp\n213: WHEN IsBeingDeleted is called with the object\n214: THEN false should be returned\n215: ```\n216: \n217: #### SCENARIO-023: HasOwnerReference returns true when owner reference exists\n218: ```gherkin\n219: GIVEN a client.Object with OwnerReferences containing an owner with UID \"test-uid\"\n220: WHEN HasOwnerReference is called with the object and UID \"test-uid\"\n221: THEN true should be returned\n222: ```\n223: \n224: #### SCENARIO-024: HasOwnerReference returns false when owner reference missing\n225: ```gherkin\n226: GIVEN a client.Object with OwnerReferences not containing UID \"missing-uid\"\n227: WHEN HasOwnerReference is called with the object and UID \"missing-uid\"\n228: THEN false should be returned\n229: ```\n230: \n231: #### SCENARIO-025: AddOwnerReference adds owner reference to object\n232: ```gherkin\n233: GIVEN a child client.Object\n234: AND an owner client.Object\n235: WHEN AddOwnerReference is called with child and owner\n236: THEN the child should have the owner in its OwnerReferences\n237: AND the owner reference should have the correct APIVersion, Kind, UID, and Name\n238: ```\n239: \n240: #### SCENARIO-026: AddLabels adds labels to object\n241: ```gherkin\n242: GIVEN a client.Object with labels = {\"existing\": \"value\"}\n243: WHEN AddLabels is called with labels = {\"new\": \"label\"}\n244: THEN the object should have labels = {\"existing\": \"value\", \"new\": \"label\"}\n245: ```\n246: \n247: #### SCENARIO-027: AddLabels initializes empty labels map\n248: ```gherkin\n249: GIVEN a client.Object with nil labels\n250: WHEN AddLabels is called with labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n251: THEN the object should have labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n252: ```\n253: \n254: #### SCENARIO-028: AddAnnotations adds annotations to object\n255: ```gherkin\n256: GIVEN a client.Object with annotations = {\"existing\": \"value\"}\n257: WHEN AddAnnotations is called with annotations = {\"new\": \"annotation\"}\n258: THEN the object should have annotations = {\"existing\": \"value\", \"new\": \"annotation\"}\n259: ```\n260: \n261: #### SCENARIO-029: IsPodReady returns true for ready pod\n262: ```gherkin\n263: GIVEN a Pod with PodReady condition status = ConditionTrue\n264: WHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\n265: THEN true should be returned\n266: ```\n267: \n268: #### SCENARIO-030: IsPodReady returns false for not ready pod\n269: ```gherkin\n270: GIVEN a Pod with PodReady condition status = ConditionFalse\n271: WHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\n272: THEN false should be returned\n273: ```\n274: \n275: #### SCENARIO-031: IsPodReady returns false for pod without ready condition\n276: ```gherkin\n277: GIVEN a Pod without PodReady condition\n278: WHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\n279: THEN false should be returned\n280: ```\n281: \n282: #### SCENARIO-032: GetPodCondition returns matching condition\n283: ```gherkin\n284: GIVEN a Pod with conditions including PodReady\n285: WHEN GetPodCondition is called with PodReady type\n286: THEN the PodReady condition should be returned\n287: ```\n288: \n289: #### SCENARIO-033: GetPodCondition returns nil for missing condition\n290: ```gherkin\n291: GIVEN a Pod without Ready condition\n292: WHEN GetPodCondition is called with Ready type\n293: THEN nil should be returned\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ### REQ-003: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/finalizers.go\n299: \n300: **Description:** Implement unit tests for finalizer management functions.\n301: \n302: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n303: \n304: #### SCENARIO-034: AddFinalizer adds finalizer to object\n305: ```gherkin\n306: GIVEN a context\n307: AND a mock client.Client\n308: AND a client.Object without finalizers\n309: WHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n310: THEN the object should have \"test-finalizer\" in its finalizers list\n311: AND no error should be returned\n312: ```\n313: \n314: #### SCENARIO-035: AddFinalizer does not add duplicate finalizer\n315: ```gherkin\n316: GIVEN a context\n317: AND a mock client.Client\n318: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"existing\", \"test-finalizer\"]\n319: WHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n320: THEN the object should still have only two finalizers\n321: AND no error should be returned\n322: ```\n323: \n324: #### SCENARIO-036: AddFinalizer handles patch error\n325: ```gherkin\n326: GIVEN a context\n327: AND a mock client.Client that returns an error on Patch\n328: AND a client.Object without finalizers\n329: WHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n330: THEN an error should be returned\n331: AND the error message should contain \"failed to add finalizer\"\n332: ```\n333: \n334: #### SCENARIO-037: RemoveFinalizer removes finalizer from object\n335: ```gherkin\n336: GIVEN a context\n337: AND a mock client.Client\n338: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"keep-me\", \"remove-me\"]\n339: WHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"remove-me\"\n340: THEN the object should have only [\"keep-me\"] in its finalizers\n341: AND no error should be returned\n342: ```\n343: \n344: #### SCENARIO-038: RemoveFinalizer does nothing when finalizer not present\n345: ```gherkin\n346: GIVEN a context\n347: AND a mock client.Client\n348: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"keep-me\"]\n349: WHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"not-present\"\n350: THEN the object should still have [\"keep-me\"] in its finalizers\n351: AND no error should be returned\n352: ```\n353: \n354: #### SCENARIO-039: RemoveFinalizer handles patch error\n355: ```gherkin\n356: GIVEN a context\n357: AND a mock client.Client that returns an error on Patch\n358: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"test-finalizer\"]\n359: WHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n360: THEN an error should be returned\n361: AND the error message should contain \"failed to remove finalizer\"\n362: ```\n363: \n364: #### SCENARIO-040: HasFinalizer returns true when finalizer present\n365: ```gherkin\n366: GIVEN a client.Object with finalizers = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]\n367: WHEN HasFinalizer is called with \"b\"\n368: THEN true should be returned\n369: ```\n370: \n371: #### SCENARIO-041: HasFinalizer returns false when finalizer absent\n372: ```gherkin\n373: GIVEN a client.Object with finalizers = [\"a\", \"c\"]\n374: WHEN HasFinalizer is called with \"b\"\n375: THEN false should be returned\n376: ```\n377: \n378: #### SCENARIO-042: GetOwnerReference returns UID when matching owner found\n379: ```gherkin\n380: GIVEN a metav1.Object with OwnerReferences\n381: AND one reference has APIVersion = \"v1\", Kind = \"Pod\", and UID = \"test-uid\"\n382: WHEN GetOwnerReference is called with APIVersion = \"v1\" and Kind = \"Pod\"\n383: THEN \"test-uid\" and true should be returned\n384: ```\n385: \n386: #### SCENARIO-043: GetOwnerReference returns empty when no matching owner\n387: ```gherkin\n388: GIVEN a metav1.Object with OwnerReferences\n389: AND none have the specified APIVersion and Kind\n390: WHEN GetOwnerReference is called with non-matching APIVersion and Kind\n391: THEN empty string and false should be returned\n392: ```\n393: \n394: ---\n395: \n396: ### REQ-004: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/status.go\n397: \n398: **Description:** Implement unit tests for status condition management functions.\n399: \n400: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n401: \n402: #### SCENARIO-044: SetCondition adds new condition to empty list\n403: ```gherkin\n404: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n405: AND a conditionType, status, reason, and message\n406: WHEN SetCondition is called\n407: THEN a new condition should be added to the list\n408: AND the condition should have the specified type, status, reason, and message\n409: AND LastTransitionTime should be set to current time\n410: ```\n411: \n412: #### SCENARIO-045: SetCondition updates existing condition with new status\n413: ```gherkin\n414: GIVEN a conditions list with a Ready condition with status = False\n415: AND new status = True\n416: WHEN SetCondition is called with Ready type and new status\n417: THEN the Ready condition should be updated to status = True\n418: AND LastTransitionTime should be updated to current time\n419: ```\n420: \n421: #### SCENARIO-046: SetCondition updates existing condition with same status\n422: ```gherkin\n423: GIVEN a conditions list with a Ready condition with status = True\n424: AND new status = True\n425: WHEN SetCondition is called with Ready type and same status\n426: THEN the Ready condition should retain status = True\n427: AND LastTransitionTime should be updated to current time\n428: AND reason and message should be updated\n429: ```\n430: \n431: #### SCENARIO-047: GetCondition returns matching condition\n432: ```gherkin\n433: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready, Available, and Progressing conditions\n434: WHEN GetCondition is called with Ready type\n435: THEN the Ready condition should be returned\n436: ```\n437: \n438: #### SCENARIO-048: GetCondition returns nil for missing condition type\n439: ```gherkin\n440: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n441: WHEN GetCondition is called with Error type\n442: THEN nil should be returned\n443: ```\n444: \n445: #### SCENARIO-049: IsReady returns true when Ready condition is true\n446: ```gherkin\n447: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition status = ConditionTrue\n448: WHEN IsReady is called\n449: THEN true should be returned\n450: ```\n451: \n452: #### SCENARIO-050: IsReady returns false when Ready condition is false\n453: ```gherkin\n454: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition status = ConditionFalse\n455: WHEN IsReady is called\n456: THEN false should be returned\n457: ```\n458: \n459: #### SCENARIO-051: IsReady returns false when Ready condition missing\n460: ```gherkin\n461: GIVEN a conditions list without Ready condition\n462: WHEN IsReady is called\n463: THEN false should be returned\n464: ```\n465: \n466: #### SCENARIO-052: IsAvailable returns true when Available condition is true\n467: ```gherkin\n468: GIVEN a conditions list with Available condition status = ConditionTrue\n469: WHEN IsAvailable is called\n470: THEN true should be returned\n471: ```\n472: \n473: #### SCENARIO-053: IsProgressing returns true when Progressing condition is true\n474: ```gherkin\n475: GIVEN a conditions list with Progressing condition status = ConditionTrue\n476: WHEN IsProgressing is called\n477: THEN true should be returned\n478: ```\n479: \n480: #### SCENARIO-054: HasError returns true when Error condition is true\n481: ```gherkin\n482: GIVEN a conditions list with Error condition status = ConditionTrue\n483: WHEN HasError is called\n484: THEN true should be returned\n485: ```\n486: \n487: #### SCENARIO-055: SetReadyCondition sets Ready condition to true\n488: ```gherkin\n489: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n490: WHEN SetReadyCondition is called with ready = true\n491: THEN a Ready condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n492: ```\n493: \n494: #### SCENARIO-056: SetReadyCondition sets Ready condition to false\n495: ```gherkin\n496: GIVEN a conditions pointer with Ready condition\n497: WHEN SetReadyCondition is called with ready = false\n498: THEN the Ready condition should have status = ConditionFalse\n499: ```\n500: \n501: #### SCENARIO-057: SetErrorCondition sets Error condition with error message\n502: ```gherkin\n503: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n504: AND an error with message \"test error\"\n505: WHEN SetErrorCondition is called with the error\n506: THEN an Error condition should be added\n507: AND the message should contain \"test error\"\n508: ```\n509: \n510: #### SCENARIO-058: SetErrorCondition sets Error condition without error\n511: ```gherkin\n512: GIVEN a conditions pointer\n513: AND nil error\n514: WHEN SetErrorCondition is called with nil error\n515: THEN an Error condition with empty message should be set\n516: ```\n517: \n518: #### SCENARIO-059: ClearErrorCondition removes Error condition\n519: ```gherkin\n520: GIVEN a conditions list with Error condition\n521: WHEN ClearErrorCondition is called\n522: THEN the Error condition should be removed from the list\n523: ```\n524: \n525: #### SCENARIO-060: ClearErrorCondition does nothing when Error condition missing\n526: ```gherkin\n527: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n528: WHEN ClearErrorCondition is called\n529: THEN the conditions list should remain unchanged\n530: ```\n531: \n532: #### SCENARIO-061: SetProgressingCondition sets Progressing condition\n533: ```gherkin\n534: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n535: WHEN SetProgressingCondition is called with progressing = true\n536: THEN a Progressing condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n537: ```\n538: \n539: #### SCENARIO-062: SetAvailableCondition sets Available condition\n540: ```gherkin\n541: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n542: WHEN SetAvailableCondition is called with available = true\n543: THEN an Available condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n544: ```\n545: \n546: #### SCENARIO-063: SetSandboxCreatedCondition sets SandboxCreated condition\n547: ```gherkin\n548: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n549: WHEN SetSandboxCreatedCondition is called with created = true\n550: THEN a SandboxCreated condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n551: ```\n552: \n553: #### SCENARIO-064: GetConditionMessage returns condition message\n554: ```gherkin\n555: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition message = \"ready message\"\n556: WHEN GetConditionMessage is called with Ready type\n557: THEN \"ready message\" should be returned\n558: ```\n559: \n560: #### SCENARIO-065: GetConditionMessage returns empty string for missing condition\n561: ```gherkin\n562: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n563: WHEN GetConditionMessage is called with Error type\n564: THEN empty string should be returned\n565: ```\n566: \n567: #### SCENARIO-066: GetConditionReason returns condition reason\n568: ```gherkin\n569: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition reason = \"ReadyReason\"\n570: WHEN GetConditionReason is called with Ready type\n571: THEN \"ReadyReason\" should be returned\n572: ```\n573: \n574: #### SCENARIO-067: GetConditionReason returns empty string for missing condition\n575: ```gherkin\n576: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n577: WHEN GetConditionReason is called with Error type\n578: THEN empty string should be returned\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ### REQ-005: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/errors.go\n584: \n585: **Description:** Implement unit tests for ReconcilerError types and constructors.\n586: \n587: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n588: \n589: #### SCENARIO-068: ReconcilerError.Error returns formatted message with wrapped error\n590: ```gherkin\n591: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"TestCode\", Message = \"Test message\", and Err = errors.New(\"wrapped\")\n592: WHEN Error is called\n593: THEN the result should contain \"TestCode: Test message (caused by: wrapped)\"\n594: ```\n595: \n596: #### SCENARIO-069: ReconcilerError.Error returns formatted message without wrapped error\n597: ```gherkin\n598: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"TestCode\", Message = \"Test message\", and Err = nil\n599: WHEN Error is called\n600: THEN the result should be \"TestCode: Test message\"\n601: ```\n602: \n603: #### SCENARIO-070: ReconcilerError.Unwrap returns wrapped error\n604: ```gherkin\n605: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Err = errors.New(\"wrapped\")\n606: WHEN Unwrap is called\n607: THEN the wrapped error should be returned\n608: ```\n609: \n610: #### SCENARIO-071: ReconcilerError.Unwrap returns nil when no wrapped error\n611: ```gherkin\n612: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Err = nil\n613: WHEN Unwrap is called\n614: THEN nil should be returned\n615: ```\n616: \n617: #### SCENARIO-072: NewReconcilerError creates error with all fields\n618: ```gherkin\n619: GIVEN code, message, err, and retryable parameters\n620: WHEN NewReconcilerError is called\n621: THEN a ReconcilerError with all fields set should be returned\n622: ```\n623: \n624: #### SCENARIO-073: NewValidationFailedError creates non-retryable error\n625: ```gherkin\n626: GIVEN message and err parameters\n627: WHEN NewValidationFailedError is called\n628: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"ValidationFailed\" and Retryable = false should be returned\n629: ```\n630: \n631: #### SCENARIO-074: NewSandboxCreateFailedError creates retryable error\n632: ```gherkin\n633: GIVEN message and err parameters\n634: WHEN NewSandboxCreateFailedError is called\n635: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxCreateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n636: ```\n637: \n638: #### SCENARIO-075: NewSandboxUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n639: ```gherkin\n640: GIVEN message and err parameters\n641: WHEN NewSandboxUpdateFailedError is called\n642: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n643: ```\n644: \n645: #### SCENARIO-076: NewSandboxDeleteFailedError creates retryable error\n646: ```gherkin\n647: GIVEN message and err parameters\n648: WHEN NewSandboxDeleteFailedError is called\n649: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n650: ```\n651: \n652: #### SCENARIO-077: NewStatusUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n653: ```gherkin\n654: GIVEN message and err parameters\n655: WHEN NewStatusUpdateFailedError is called\n656: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"StatusUpdateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n657: ```\n658: \n659: #### SCENARIO-078: NewFinalizerFailedError creates retryable error\n660: ```gherkin\n661: GIVEN message and err parameters\n662: WHEN NewFinalizerFailedError is called\n663: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"FinalizerFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n664: ```\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ### REQ-006: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/controller.go\n669: \n670: **Description:** Implement unit tests for controller setup and configuration functions.\n671: \n672: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n673: \n674: #### SCENARIO-079: DefaultControllerConfig returns sensible defaults\n675: ```gherkin\n676: GIVEN no configuration provided\n677: WHEN DefaultControllerConfig is called\n678: THEN RequeueAfter should be 10 seconds\n679: AND MaxConcurrentReconciles should be 2\n680: AND EnableLeaderElection should be true\n681: AND LeaderElectionID should be \"agentcube-reconciler\"\n682: ```\n683: \n684: #### SCENARIO-080: NewControllerManager creates manager with config\n685: ```gherkin\n686: GIVEN a rest.Config\n687: AND a ControllerConfig with custom values\n688: WHEN NewControllerManager is called\n689: THEN a ctrl.Manager should be returned\n690: AND the manager should use the specified scheme\n691: AND no error should be returned\n692: ```\n693: \n694: #### SCENARIO-081: NewControllerManager handles error from ctrl.NewManager\n695: ```gherkin\n696: GIVEN an invalid rest.Config\n697: AND a ControllerConfig\n698: WHEN NewControllerManager is called\n699: THEN an error should be returned\n700: AND the error message should contain \"unable to start manager\"\n701: ```\n702: \n703: #### SCENARIO-082: GetSandboxName returns formatted name\n704: ```gherkin\n705: GIVEN a workload name \"test-workload\"\n706: WHEN GetSandboxName is called\n707: THEN \"test-workload-sandbox\" should be returned\n708: ```\n709: \n710: #### SCENARIO-083: GetSandboxName handles empty workload name\n711: ```gherkin\n712: GIVEN an empty workload name\n713: WHEN GetSandboxName is called\n714: THEN \"-sandbox\" should be returned\n715: ```\n716: \n717: ---\n718: \n719: ### REQ-007: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/metrics.go\n720: \n721: **Description:** Implement unit tests for Prometheus metrics recording functions.\n722: \n723: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n724: \n725: #### SCENARIO-084: RecordReconciliation increments reconcileTotal counter\n726: ```gherkin\n727: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n728: WHEN RecordReconciliation is called with controller, namespace, name, duration, and result\n729: THEN reconcileTotal counter should be incremented\n730: AND reconcileDuration histogram should observe the duration\n731: ```\n732: \n733: #### SCENARIO-085: RecordReconciliation increments reconcileRequeues on error result\n734: ```gherkin\n735: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n736: WHEN RecordReconciliation is called with result = \"error\"\n737: THEN reconcileRequeues counter should be incremented\n738: ```\n739: \n740: #### SCENARIO-086: RecordReconciliationError increments reconcileErrors counter\n741: ```gherkin\n742: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n743: WHEN RecordReconciliationError is called\n744: THEN reconcileErrors counter should be incremented\n745: ```\n746: \n747: #### SCENARIO-087: RecordRequeue increments reconcileRequeues counter\n748: ```gherkin\n749: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n750: WHEN RecordRequeue is called\n751: THEN reconcileRequeues counter should be incremented\n752: ```\n753: \n754: #### SCENARIO-088: RecordResourceReady increments resourcesReady gauge\n755: ```gherkin\n756: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n757: WHEN RecordResourceReady is called\n758: THEN resourcesReady gauge should be incremented\n759: ```\n760: \n761: #### SCENARIO-089: RecordResourcePending increments resourcesPending gauge\n762: ```gherkin\n763: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n764: WHEN RecordResourcePending is called\n765: THEN resourcesPending gauge should be incremented\n766: ```\n767: \n768: #### SCENARIO-090: RecordResourceError increments resourcesError gauge\n769: ```gherkin\n770: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n771: WHEN RecordResourceError is called\n772: THEN resourcesError gauge should be incremented\n773: ```\n774: \n775: #### SCENARIO-091: ClearResourceMetrics resets resource gauges to zero\n776: ```gherkin\n777: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics with non-zero values\n778: WHEN ClearResourceMetrics is called\n779: THEN resourcesReady gauge should be set to 0\n780: AND resourcesPending gauge should be set to 0\n781: AND resourcesError gauge should be set to 0\n782: ```\n783: \n784: #### SCENARIO-092: RecordSandboxCreation increments sandboxCreations counter\n785: ```gherkin\n786: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n787: WHEN RecordSandboxCreation is called\n788: THEN sandboxCreations counter should be incremented\n789: AND sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration\n790: ```\n791: \n792: #### SCENARIO-093: RecordSandboxDeletion increments sandboxDeletions counter\n793: ```gherkin\n794: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n795: WHEN RecordSandboxDeletion is called\n796: THEN sandboxDeletions counter should be incremented\n797: AND sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration\n798: ```\n799: \n800: #### SCENARIO-094: RecordSandboxUpdate records update duration\n801: ```gherkin\n802: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n803: WHEN RecordSandboxUpdate is called\n804: THEN sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration with operation = \"update\"\n805: ```\n806: \n807: #### SCENARIO-095: ResetMetrics resets all metrics\n808: ```gherkin\n809: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics with non-zero values\n810: WHEN ResetMetrics is called\n811: THEN all metric counters should be reset\n812: AND all metric histograms should be reset\n813: AND all metric gauges should be reset\n814: ```\n815: \n816: ---\n817: \n818: ## Non-Requirements (Excluded from this task)\n819: \n820: The following files are excluded as they contain only constants, plain structs, or are better tested with integration tests:\n821: \n822: - `defaults.go` - Contains only constants\n823: - `api/types.go` - Contains only plain struct definitions\n824: - `types/sandbox_types.go` - Contains only plain struct definitions\n825: - `server/server.go` - Server lifecycle is better tested with integration/end-to-end tests\n826: - `controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` - Complex reconciler logic is better tested with integration tests using envtest\n827: \n828: ---\n829: \n830: ## Test Coverage Goals\n831: \n832: Target coverage: **≥ 80%** for all tested files\n833: \n834: Priority order:\n835: 1. `auth/k8s_auth.go` - Critical security component\n836: 2. `controller/reconciler/predicates.go` - Core event filtering logic\n837: 3. `controller/reconciler/finalizers.go` - Resource cleanup safety\n838: 4. `controller/reconciler/status.go` - State management\n839: 5. `controller/reconciler/errors.go` - Error handling\n840: 6. `controller/reconciler/controller.go` - Controller setup\n841: 7. `controller/reconciler/metrics.go` - Observability\n842: \n843: ---\n844: \n845: ## Dependencies\n846: \n847: - `k8s.io/client-go` - Kubernetes client library (for mocks in auth tests)\n848: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` - Controller runtime (for mock client in reconciler tests)\n849: - `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` - Prometheus client (for metrics tests)\n850: - `github.com/stretchr/testify` - Testing assertions and mocks\n851: - `github.com/golang/mock` - Mock generation for k8s interfaces\n\n(End of file - total 851 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec: AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nModule: `pkg/workloadmanager`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: L\nTask: Add comprehensive unit tests for untested components\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Unit tests for auth/k8s_auth.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for K8sAuthenticator and TokenCache components.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-001: K8sAuthenticator authenticates valid token\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775892943936,"end":1775892943942}}}}
